Hi James,

Great kick-off on Friday. Summarising key decisions for the record.

SAMPLE: n=1,070 respondents, nationally representative UK sample. Fieldwork August 2023.

SEGMENTATION (core variable: purchase intent after concept exposure):
- probable_trialists: respondents who "would definitely" or "would probably" buy Stocked
- non_probable: would not buy
- buy_regularly: already buy frozen ready meals regularly
- buy_occasionally: occasional buyers
- try_once: would try once but not commit

INDEX CONVENTION: An index of 100 = total sample average. Above 100 = over-indexing. For example, probable_trialists_spend_index of 151.77 means probable trialists spend 51.77% more than average.

VARIABLE NAMING: {segment}_{metric}_{measure}. Examples:
- probable_trialists_spend_avg = average monthly GBP spend among probable trialists
- buy_regularly_share_of_wallet_share = share of wallet for regular buyers
- total_sample_preference_sample_size = sample size for preference in total sample

RTE = ready-to-eat. Variable rte_categories_bought_in_p1m tracks which RTE categories were purchased in the past month.

Questionnaire covers: demographics, category behaviour, cooking habits, needs assessment (45+ items), concept evaluation, and competition (19 meal categories rated 0-10).

Draft questionnaire by Wednesday.

